Junior High football practice will begin Monday Aug. 17 at 3:30

Junior High volleyball practice will begin Monday Aug. 17 from 5:30-7:00. When school starts, practice will begin at 3:30.

All athletes must have a physical on file prior to beginning practice. They may bring the form with them on the first day of practice.

Athletes will need to bring their own water bottles. Football will be able to use water jugs to fill their bottles. Volleyball will be able to use the bottle filling stations in the gym.

Per MSHSAA recommendations, all athletes must wear a face covering when entering and exiting the building and while not engaged in strenuous physical activity.

post_text:
We are excited to be able to host the junior/senior prom on July 10th at the Lake View Event Barn with the promenade beginning at 5.
Please have your kids:
1. Check their school email for the invitation and have them RSVP to Ms. Bolser no later than Monday, July 6th.

2. Make sure they and their date have a signed waiver and bring it with them or Mrs. Bollig will be at the library on Tuesday and Wednesday from 9 am to 2 pm if anyone needed to stop by and get one or drop if off.
- All attendees HAVE to have a signed waiver in order to attend the prom. Students will not be permitted to enter the venue without one.

3. Make sure they have a photo order form if they need it, bring money and order with them to give to Robyn the day of prom.

4. Please watch the Facebook Page and or emails for updates next week.

post_text:
To the parents of students entering the 12th grade next year:
It is required by Missouri state law that all students entering the 12th grade must have a Meningitis vaccine prior to beginning the first day of school. It was our intention to hold an on-site shot clinic at school, however due too uncontrollable circumstances that will not be possible at this time. You may take your child to the health care provider of your choice to have this shot done. I have been contacted by the Appleton City Clinic stating that they currently have the needed vaccine available. You may call ahead so you and your child will not have to sit in the waiting room. Please make sure you have a copy of the vaccine received provided to the school nurse.

post_text: This is an update on how grades will be calculated for second semester. For seniors, third quarter grades will also be their second semester grades. For all other students, we will not calculate second semester grades until we return in the fall. The first two weeks back in school will be considered make-up time. During this time, students will be able to make up work from third quarter. At the end of those two weeks, grades will be entered for third quarter, and that grade will also be the semester grade. If you have any questions, feel free to contact the school tomorrow during business hours or email me at jgurney@appletoncity.k12.mo.us. Have a wonderful day!

Starting Friday night on April 10th, ACHS will be joining schools around the country by turning on our football stadium lights on Friday night at 8:20 p.m., which is 20:20 military time, and leaving them lit for 20 minutes, and 20 seconds to honor the class of 2020. We want all community members to be aware in the event someone is wondering why our stadium lights are on.

At 8:20 p.m. on Friday night look toward The Bulldog Field of Pride to see the glow of our support for our graduating class of 2020.

Please, continue to follow CDC guidance and stay safe and healthy. We miss all of our students and staff!

shared_text:
Sarah Leiber‎Appleton City FFA Chapter
April 4 at 6:30 PM ·

Due to the Governor's stay at home order the AC FFA Greenhouse will be closed till April 24th to the general public. No one will be able to enter the greenhouse. You will be able to do pick up orders or knock if my car is there while I'm watering. Orders can be made by text, phone call or Facebook messager. Mrs. Leiber's cell phone number is 660-424-3668. We will then arrange a pickup time. Please plan on paying using a check to cut down on the contamination risks to all involved.
The FFA cares about all our community and want them to stay safe during these times.

post_text: The school board meeting tomorrow night will begin at 7:15 in the library. In order to stay in compliance with the orders of the governor, which states that no more than 10 people shall gather in any one place, the meeting will be closed to the public. It will, however be streamed via Facebook live on this site. If anyone does not have access to Facebook, but still wishes to view the meeting, we will open classrooms and show the stream on the Smartboards. We will open up as many classrooms as needed to accommodate everyone present. The classrooms will be limited to no more than 10 people, and everyone present is urged to practice appropriate social distancing. The purpose of the stream will be to grant everyone equal access to the meeting. It will not be a question/answer session as our previous live session was. If you have any questions, please call the central office at 660-476-2161 during business hours tomorrow.

Dear Parents:
We would like to remind you that Missouri requires all students entering the 8th grade to receive a Tdap and Meningitis shot and all students entering the 12th grade to receive a Meningitis shot prior to the first day of school in August. For your convenience, we will be offering a free shot clinic at school on Wednesday, March 4th for those students who are currently in the 7th and 11th grades. If your child needs these vaccines, the required forms have been mailed to your home address for you to complete and return to school. If you have any questions please contact the school nurse at (660)476-2161 option #7.

Good afternoon. This is an update on our school calendar and how we are going to handle snow make up days. Beginning Wednesday February 26th, all early-out Wednesdays will be lengthened to full days, following the normal bell schedule of 8 am to 3:13 pm.

Beginning March 2nd, 6 minutes will be added to the school day. School will still begin at 8 AM, but dismissal time will be 3:19 PM. Also, please note that March 6th, which was originally scheduled to be an early release day, will now be a full day of school. The last day of school has been changed from May 12th to May 13th, and dismissal will be at 12:15 on that day.

post_text:
Fans attending the football game Friday night, and any subsequent playoff games held here:

Following is a list of requirements for fans attending MSHSAA sponsored District/State contests.

The following items are NOT allowed at the games:

Confetti/shredded paper
Laser pointers/flashing objects
Megaphones
Compressed air horns/sirens
Whistles
Drones
Cannons/Fireworks
Animals/Pets (other than service animals with proper credential documentation)
Fans are not allowed on the field at any time (team introduction/run-throughs)

Even though some of these things have been allowed to go on during the regular season, during the District/State playoffs, the State Association restricts the use of these items, and host schools are responsible for enforcing the regulations. Our kids and coaches have worked extremely hard to get to this level, and we don’t want to do anything that may cause a distraction or penalization of our team. Thank you for your cooperation. If you have any questions, please contact the high school office at 660-476-2118.

ATTENTION MONTROSE AND APPLETON CITY HIGH SCHOOL GIRLS: Softball practice will begin on Monday, August 12 at 7 pm. There will be a parent/player meeting beginning at 7 pm immediately following the Open House. Practice will begin as soon as the meeting is over. PARENTS--You are invited to stay and observe practice following the meeting. Practice will be over by 9:30 pm.

Food Service Survey

Appleton City Elementary School
May 7, 2019 at 10:54 AM ·

To members of the Appleton City R-II Community,

We are coming to the end of the 2018-2019 school year and also the first year of our participation in OPAA, our new cafeteria program. It's time to take stock of how things have gone this year and to hear how you feel about whether breakfast, lunches and other food services under OPAA has been successful. It is the District's intention to do this kind of survey every year. The results of this survey are very important to our District and will be a key factor in determining how food service will be done here going forward. We will deliver the survey in both web-based and paper form and will accept completed paper surveys in the Elementary, High School, and District offices. Thank you for your participation.

Joe Dunlap
Appleton City R-II Superintendent

To members of the Appleton City R-II Community,

We are coming to the end of the 2018-2019 school year and also the first year of our participation in OPAA, our new cafeteria program. It’s time to take stock of how things have gone this year and to hear how you feel about whether breakfast, lunches and other food services under OPAA has been successful. It is the District’s intention to do this kind of survey every year. The results of this survey are very important to our District and will be a key factor in determining how food service will be done here going forward. We will deliver the survey in both web-based and paper form and will accept completed paper surveys in the Elementary, High School, and District offices. Thank you for your participation.

Joe Dunlap

Appleton City R-II Superintendent

post_text: All your veggie and flower needs are being sold in our FFA Greenhouse. Sale starts this Monday April 22nd.
shared_text:
Sarah Leiber‎Appleton City FFA Chapter
April 12, 2019 at 3:15 PM ·

Appleton City FFA Plant Sale
The AC FFA will be holding their spring plant sale starting on April 22nd. The FFA greenhouse will be open for business from 7:45 am to 3:30 pm on all school days as well as Saturday April 27th from 12-4 pm, just stop by the Agriculture building for assistance any weekday. The FFA has garden vegetables and flowers for sale such as tomatoes, broccoli, cabbage and peppers as well as potting flowers like petunias, annual vinca, impatiens and geraniums. Flowers and vegetables can be purchased as four or six packs, individuals or as hanging baskets. Costs are $2.00/ four packs, $1/Tomato Plant, and $12/Hanging Basket or 3 Hanging baskets for $10 each. For more information feel free to give Mrs. Leiber a call at 660-424-3668.
